  "A low work function reduces the temperature of the solar panel": "",
  "A metal with a low work function has a lower threshold frequency, meaning a broader range of the solar spectrum (including lower-frequency light) can eject electrons. This allows the solar panel to convert more of the incoming sunlight into electrical energy.": "",
  "A student shines light of frequency 8.0 × 10¹⁴ Hz on a metal with a work function of 3.0 eV. Using E = hf with h = 6.63 × 10⁻³⁴ J·s and 1 eV = 1.6 × 10⁻¹⁹ J, which statement is correct?": "",
